  "prompt": "What is the best comedy movie ever?",
  "response": "Determining the \"best\" comedy movie ever is subjective and can vary widely based on personal taste. However, several films are frequently cited as among the greatest in the genre. Some popular contenders include:\n\n1. **Monty Python and the Holy Grail** (1975) - A classic British comedy known for its absurd humor and memorable lines.\n2. **Airplane!** (1980) - A parody of disaster films filled with visual gags and wordplay.\n3. **Some Like It Hot** (1959) - A Billy Wilder classic featuring Tony Curtis and Jack Lemmon in a tale of mistaken identity.\n4. **The Big Lebowski** (1998) - A cult favorite by the Coen Brothers, known for its eccentric characters and quotable dialogue.\n5. **Groundhog Day** (1993) - A unique blend of comedy and existential reflection starring Bill Murray.\n\nUltimately, the best comedy movie for you may depend on your sense of humor and the kind of comedic style you enjoy!",
